<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-091-048  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 091 048.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  August 1989 v6 n8 p27(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Leading E-mail vendors introduce X.400 gateway API. (the X.400Application Program Interface Association)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Morris, Larry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The X.400 Application Program Interface Assoc (APIA) , a coalitionof communications and computer industry vendors, define the APIfor the X.400 gateway interface.andP;  The eventual goal for thespecification will be to assure that any user can exchangeelectronic messages with any other user, regardless of thegeography, network, or type of hardware or software being used.andO;Gateways translate the features of one e-mail package to another,allowing communication.andP;  The X.400 Gateway API represents a trueopen systems connection, and is based on the X.400 protocolsadopted by the International Telegraph and Telephone ConsultativeCommittee and the International Standards Organization as part ofthe Open Systems Interconnection.andP;  Membership in the APIA is opento any organization for a $5,000 membership fee and a statementpledging compliance to the standard.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electronic Mail SystemsApplications ProgrammingX.400 ProtocolGateways (Interface)StandardizationOpen SystemsInterfaceX.400 Application Program Interface Association.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>